EpBench — The Tulving Episodic Memory Benchmark
================================================

The benchmark, its dataset, and its evaluation harness are the work of:

  Zied Ben Houidi and Alexis Huet (Huawei Technologies France)
  "The Tulving Episodic Memory Benchmark"
  Accepted at ICLR 2025.
  arXiv: 2501.13121
  Upstream repository: https://github.com/ahstat/episodic-memory-benchmark
  License: MIT (© 2024-2025 the authors)

This directory does NOT redistribute the upstream dataset (the generated
"books" and Q&A). To reproduce, obtain the data from the upstream repository
and its figshare release, then apply the Compresh arm and scripts in `code/`
(see REPRODUCE.md).

What is original to Compresh here:
  - the Compresh (TUL 2.0) answering arm and the runner/scoring scripts in
    `code/` (MIT, © 2026 Compresh Ltd),
  - the computed results in `results/` and the analysis in this README.

Scores in `results/` are produced with the benchmark's OWN scoring functions
(epbench.src.evaluation.ranking), so they are directly comparable to the
numbers published in the upstream repository.
